rComments: amazing teacher, interesting lectures

Prof Desjardins est un très bon prof! Le cours est très intéressant. le semestre était en ligne et j'ai apprécié le fait que chaque powerpoint avait un enregistrement audio inclus. Professeur Desjardins a pris aussi l'effort de tenir aussi des sessions synchrones le lundi en plus des powerpoint pré-enregistrés.
He knows his stuff super well and he is straightforward with what he expects from you. Sometimes he says stuff in lecture that's not on his slides so it is important to listen carefully.
Great prof, only need to study powerpoints. Good at explaining tricky concepts
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Amazing lectures ', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Amazing prof, best one I've had so far at OttawaU!! Make sure you study the pp for the midterms and final I guarantee you will have an A. He explains everything so clearly. He is very passionate about what he teaches so you'll never be bored in his class. He is fair in his exams so make sure you study! Textbook is useless, don't buy it.

Desjardins is one of my favourite profs that I've ever had at uOttawa. The course itself was very interesting and he did a wonderful job portraying the subject matter. I loved attending his lectures as he would explain everything really well and add interesting anecdotes. His tests are fair and he gives lots of hints in class. Highly recommend.

Dr Desjardins is the best teacher I've had so far. Everything's on his PP, the textbook is useless. If you take this class, you should stard studying at least a week before your exam: there's a LOT of content to know by heart.

Final exam was easy, finished it in an hour. Midterms can be tricky, make sure to study in advance because you need to remember everything by heart. Exams are fair though. 2 midterms of 30 multiple choices each for 30% of final grade each + final exam (60 multiple choices 10 true/falses and 3 big questions that he hints in class) for 40%.

Amazing prof, you can tell he's passionate about what he teaches. However, this class isn't as easy as people say it is... His exams are very tricky and there's a LOT of content so make sure you study in advance and memorizing everything. Go to class!! He hints things that are actually on the exam so its pretty helpful going.

Super bon prof. Il connais clairement sa matière puis est passionné par la microbio et immuno. Ses diapo sont très complète. Il faut vraiment étudier et connaitre la matière pour ce cour. Les mi-session son 30 choix multiples pour 30% de ta note Il faut être capable de facilement reconnaitre les signes et symptômes. Il donne bcp de hints en classe.

Un très bon professeur! Il est clair qu'il est passionné par sa matière. Ses explications sont très claires et ses powerpoints sont en général très complets! Il est nécessaire d'etudier pour avoir des bonnes notes, mais ses examens sont représentatifs de la matière.

Great prof teaching a great class! He's really interesting and clear. The material is pretty heavy with tons of memorization so going to class is extremely helpful.  Exams are pretty difficult so study LOTS. I studied 2 days before for 1st midterm got 67%,  studied a week before 2nd midterm got 90%.

I just took the class this semester and I actually struggled the whole time. It is not a subject you can study the day before and expect an A like I was told by so many. Exams are tricky and questions can be extremely picky.
Teacher really knows his stuff and very interesting lecture. The only thing is midterms are 30 multiple choice worth 30%, so don't mess up.

Really great prof. If you go to the lectures and pay attention you will do really well in his class. The content itself is hard but he really does care about his students and will take the time to re explain concepts to you. Tests are reflect really well what was seen in class. Would definitely recommend this prof!

Great prof! Very clear in lectures and gave many real life examples in class which made class more interesting. Took over an hour to explain a concept one-on-one just to make sure that it was clear. Only downside was the midterms were 30 MCQs for 30% and the final were formatted similarly.

Vraiment bon prof! Ses diapositives et ses explications sont très claires. Les examens mi-sessions sont extrêmement juste, malgré qu'il y a seulement 30 choix multiples pour 30% de ta note finale. Il est là pour répondre à tes questions! Matière très intéressante! Je vous le conseil définitivement.

He's a great teacher, he explains his ideas fully and knows what he's talking about. He even took an hour to explain to me and my friend the concepts we didn't understand. Which NEVER happens in University. Also, he couldn't be clearer about his expectations, if you show up and listen, you'll do great. Best class last semester!Very interesting!

Great professor, very clear explanations. He is clear about what he expects from his students and the exam questions are manageable. Learn the powerpoints by heart and you will do well. Only thing I did not like, was that the midterms were on 30 which gives little room for error to get a good grade, so you got to be good in multiple choices.

He's a good prof. The material itself isn't hard but there is a LOT to know/memorize. I wouldn't say you need to attend classes as midterms/final are 100% based on the powerpoints. Tests are multiple choice 30 MC worth 30% so it's not easy to get an A+. Good course overall.

Awesome prof! I am in French Immersion, so I am not particularly strong in French, but Dr. Desjardins was super clear and easy to understand. EVERYTHING in the exams are in his powerpoints (even says not to buy textbook). DOWNSIDE - He gives midterms of 30 MCQ for 30% of your final, so it isn't easy to get an A or A+.
I can only say amazing stuff about this prof! I definitely recommend him!
Great prof!! memorize the powerpoints and you'll ace the tests!

Favorite prof this year. I'm in french immersion so french is my second language, but I still understood his class better than lots of my english ones. Gives real world examples from his work as a microbiologist, midterms are clear and you know what to study for, don't need a textbook. amazinng :)
Awesome prof, very clear, he knows everything about his subject.One of the best prof I ever had
He is verry clear and helpful !and the class is verry interesting and exams are easy!
Excellent professeur
SUPER PROF!!!

Très bon professeur. Communique très bien la matière, donne des bons exemples, s?assure que tout le monde a compris, très bon PowerPoint. Ces examens demandent beaucoup d?étude mais cela vaut vraiment la peine. Je recommanderais le à tous!
